DETAIL
12 summers have passed and the Juice Maker has
fnally unveiled his creation. 3,600 bottles of the fnest,
purest cane juice rum ever distilled in India. Not to

American Oak barrels and a mere 6.6% of the original
flled quantity remains to be savoured by us mortals.
And so the name Camikara was chosen - derived

A celebration of land, time, culture and people.
A GIFT OF
LAND & TIME
On the nose you are greeted with a bouquet of
aromas - honey, ginger, tofee, raisin, prunes and
leather. A deeper whif reveals the wood.
Te frst sip brings a marriage of honey, vanilla & bitter
chocolate. Further savoring reveals ripe bananas, orange
peels, dark chocolate & charred wood.
When you put down the glass, you will be lef with the satiety
of enjoying a delicious fuit cake, making you want for more...
A complex sipping rum best enjoyed neat!
